00:27:07,609 --> 00:27:10,509
Score D-!

273
00:27:11,842 --> 00:27:15,071
"Truthfully, I don't call you Seung Jo."

274
00:27:15,071 --> 00:27:19,771
"I call you the 'Spirit of the Forest.'"

275
00:27:19,771 --> 00:27:22,855
Oh my God, she called him a Spirit of the Forest!

276
00:27:22,855 --> 00:27:25,040
- "If you ask why..."
- What the hell are you doing?!

277
00:27:25,040 --> 00:27:27,200
What the hell are you doing?!

278
00:27:35,275 --> 00:27:37,750
I shouldn't really have gone to such an extent...

279
00:27:37,750 --> 00:27:38,909
but...

280
00:27:38,909 --> 00:27:40,509
But?

281
00:27:40,509 --> 00:27:42,612
But what?

282
00:27:42,612 --> 00:27:45,642
I absolutely hate stupid girls.

283
00:27:47,475 --> 00:27:49,575
Where are you going!?!

284
00:27:55,075 --> 00:27:56,675
Apologize!

285
00:27:58,675 --> 00:28:00,775
You're laughing? Is this funny to you?

286
00:28:00,775 --> 00:28:02,742
Do you mind moving?

287
00:28:04,609 --> 00:28:06,509
Are you deaf? I told you to apologize!

288
00:28:06,509 --> 00:28:09,209
What do I have to apologize for?

289
00:28:09,209 --> 00:28:11,075
For correcting her mistakes?

290
00:28:11,075 --> 00:28:14,375
This little bastard... Hey hey hey!!!

291
00:28:14,375 --> 00:28:17,444
Do you only see mistakes in this?

292
00:28:17,444 --> 00:28:22,775
You should be looking at the
substance of it, not the words.
The feelings she put into it!

293
00:28:24,509 --> 00:28:28,642
Ah, you punk, you're going
to keep on doing that, huh?

294
00:28:32,242 --> 00:28:34,609
Let's do this.

295
00:28:34,609 --> 00:28:38,275
Don't just stand there, come at me!

296
00:28:41,409 --> 00:28:43,475
Did you see that?

297
00:28:43,475 --> 00:28:46,942
What? Scared? Are you scared!?

298
00:28:46,942 --> 00:28:48,950
Hey, come. Come! Bring it!

299
00:28:48,950 --> 00:28:51,770
- Come? Come? Come for what?!

300
00:28:54,209 --> 00:28:58,409
Bong Joon Gu, you! Come into my office right now!

301
00:28:58,409 --> 00:29:00,260
But, Vice Principal, that isn't it.

302
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:03,300
- Please listen to me.
- Listen? Listen to what?

303
00:29:06,209 --> 00:29:10,175
Seung Jo, don't worry about this. Go and study.

304
00:29:10,175 --> 00:29:13,575
Don't hang around with this fool.

305
00:29:15,242 --> 00:29:18,860
The top 4% is in red. Orange is the top 11%.

306
00:29:18,860 --> 00:29:21,500
Yellow has been the same for four years.

307
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:26,075
Green is just there to make
the other students look better.

308
00:29:26,075 --> 00:29:29,909
You guys are violet.
You are the embarrassment of the school.

309
00:29:29,909 --> 00:29:33,009
That's what the Vice Principal said.

310
00:29:36,209 --> 00:29:41,142
There are 50 spots for study hall this month.
They're just numbers.

311
00:29:41,142 --> 00:29:45,575
But I'm sure you realize that those numbers
signify the highest ranked students, right?

312
00:29:45,575 --> 00:29:47,880
I don't know how you can sit there laughing, writing

313
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:51,600
such useless things when that list is right here.

314
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:55,175
Are you stupid or just thick skinned?

315
00:29:55,175 --> 00:29:57,700
Regretably, I despise girls that are stupid

316
00:29:57,700 --> 00:30:02,100
whether or not they're thick skinned...

317
00:30:02,100 --> 00:30:03,942
they disgust me.

318
00:30:20,809 --> 00:30:22,585
[Baek Seung Jo]

319
00:30:25,442 --> 00:30:28,142
[Oh Ha Ni]

320
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:39,620
Stop running!

321
00:30:40,109 --> 00:30:42,175
Will you stop running already?!

322
00:30:44,275 --> 00:30:49,409
Hey, what are you doing?
You're already on your 34th lap.

323
00:30:52,142 --> 00:30:53,975
Two more.

324
00:30:55,109 --> 00:30:57,042
Two more laps.

325
00:30:59,109 --> 00:31:02,609
What is this? Is she training for
a marathon or something?

326
00:31:02,609 --> 00:31:05,075
Why is she running so much?

327
00:31:05,075 --> 00:31:08,509
Let her be.
Ha Ni likes running.

328
00:31:09,309 --> 00:31:14,175
I suppose. If you could go to university by running long distances, Oh Ha Ni would be in the lead.

329
00:31:18,309 --> 00:31:23,609
You're right. My specialty is doing anything...
for a long period of time.

330
00:31:55,175 --> 00:31:57,475
Even if I have to crawl, I'll get there.

331
00:32:31,075 --> 00:32:32,575
Me too.

332
00:32:33,042 --> 00:32:34,709
Let's go!

333
00:32:34,709 --> 00:32:37,675
Last lap, let's go!

334
00:32:46,509 --> 00:32:50,575
It's her, it's her! The one who confessed
to Baek Seung Jo and got rejected!

335
00:32:50,575 --> 00:32:53,775
I heard she was humiliated
and she wasn't even pretty.

336
00:32:53,775 --> 00:32:55,342
I don't understand women like her...

337
00:32:55,342 --> 00:32:58,742
I know!

338
00:32:58,742 --> 00:33:00,242
Seung Jo Oppa is ours though.

339
00:33:00,242 --> 00:33:04,942
- Hey, Oh Ha Ni, Oh Ha Ni...
- What?! Oh Ha Ni. What?

340
00:33:17,909 --> 00:33:19,475
Auntie, it's too much.

341
00:33:19,475 --> 00:33:23,675
You have to eat a lot to gain strength.
How else are you going to live?

342
00:33:28,109 --> 00:33:31,909
Still she's very optimistic. If it were me, I don't think
I would be able to come to school.

343
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,900
You say so? She's a senior

344
00:33:34,900 --> 00:33:36,620
yet she still doesn't know how to write Korean.

345
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:39,400
Aigoo, how frustrating.

346
00:33:51,075 --> 00:33:54,109
Ha Ni! The two story house is really nice!!

347
00:33:54,109 --> 00:33:56,742
Where did the scissors go?

348
00:33:59,042 --> 00:34:01,709
Ummm... should be...

349
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:04,300
It's here.

350
00:34:19,042 --> 00:34:20,594
Ha Ni!

351
00:34:21,775 --> 00:34:24,309
Do you know how old this table is?

352
00:34:26,775 --> 00:34:31,809
Grandma gave it to you when you
opened the noodle shop; it's older than me.

353
00:34:31,809 --> 00:34:35,109
That's right! The table is 21 years old!

354
00:34:35,109 --> 00:34:40,242
There's not even a scratch! It's really sturdy!

355
00:34:43,809 --> 00:34:48,275
When you were little...you played in here...

356
00:34:58,109 --> 00:35:00,042
Jjan~! (Surprise!).

357
00:35:06,117 --> 00:35:09,540
Ha Ni. It's a two story house.

358
00:35:09,540 --> 00:35:13,800
You sang a song about two story houses,
so how do you like it?

359
00:35:13,809 --> 00:35:15,309
I like it.

360
00:35:16,175 --> 00:35:17,642
What's going on?

361
00:35:18,242 --> 00:35:19,342
You didn't do well?

362
00:35:19,342 --> 00:35:20,175
What do you mean?

363
00:35:20,175 --> 00:35:22,509
Aah... that... let...

364
00:35:25,375 --> 00:35:26,875
Nothing.

365
00:35:29,775 --> 00:35:32,288
Aigooo~

366
00:35:35,909 --> 00:35:38,642
This was here!

367
00:35:38,642 --> 00:35:40,692
Here, look at this!

368
00:35:40,692 --> 00:35:42,442
It's super cute right?

369
00:35:43,009 --> 00:35:46,142
You were this small when you were a year old.

370
00:35:47,709 --> 00:35:48,909
You've grown up so much.

371
00:35:48,909 --> 00:35:51,475
But you are like this, rebellious now!

372
00:35:51,809 --> 00:35:53,536
I am not!

373
00:35:54,209 --> 00:35:56,942
My hand is similar to Mom's hand.

374
00:35:56,942 --> 00:35:58,271
Right?

375
00:35:58,271 --> 00:35:59,542
Huh?

376
00:36:00,509 --> 00:36:02,042
Yes.

377
00:36:16,109 --> 00:36:17,509
Dad.

378
00:36:23,642 --> 00:36:24,709
Ha Ni~

379
00:36:24,709 --> 00:36:26,109
We're here!

380
00:36:26,109 --> 00:36:26,914
I'm here too!

381
00:36:26,914 --> 00:36:30,942
Hurry up! I'm so hungry that I might die!

382
00:36:30,942 --> 00:36:32,475
Wow, it's to die for!

383
00:36:33,009 --> 00:36:35,378
Wow! This is just great!

384
00:36:35,378 --> 00:36:37,809
Wow, is this your room?

385
00:36:38,575 --> 00:36:40,742
Wow, this is great!

386
00:36:40,742 --> 00:36:43,409
It's so great here.

387
00:36:44,342 --> 00:36:48,309
Ha Ni, your house is awesome!
Two story house!

388
00:36:48,309 --> 00:36:51,909
For me, I like this the best!

389
00:36:51,909 --> 00:36:55,042
Ha Ni! Is this your foot?

390
00:36:55,042 --> 00:36:55,842
Yes.

391
00:36:55,842 --> 00:36:59,475
It's so cute.

392
00:36:59,975 --> 00:37:01,575
Hey!! Stop that! Bong Joon Gu!

393
00:37:01,575 --> 00:37:03,709
- Why?
- Come on, kids! Ha Ni, get that.

394
00:37:03,709 --> 00:37:06,309
- Yes.
- I will get that.

395
00:37:06,309 --> 00:37:08,375
I will get it.

396
00:37:08,375 --> 00:37:10,209
It smells great!

397
00:37:10,209 --> 00:37:13,042
Wow, it looks so good.
Aigoo.

398
00:37:13,042 --> 00:37:15,975
There wasn't much time so
I didn't prepare much food.

399
00:37:15,975 --> 00:37:18,709
When did you prepare all this?
This is a lot!

400
00:37:18,709 --> 00:37:20,775
This is a feast!

401
00:37:20,775 --> 00:37:22,209
Is that right?

402
00:37:22,209 --> 00:37:28,709
We're having guests from Busan today so the main menu is Busan's Mil-myun (Busan's local noodles).

403
00:37:28,709 --> 00:37:32,275
How did you know? It's my favorite.

404
00:37:32,275 --> 00:37:34,409
Wah. Thank you, dad!

405
00:37:34,942 --> 00:37:38,175
- I'll eat well!
- I'll eat well!!

406
00:37:43,400 --> 00:37:44,645
Father! Hmm?

407
00:37:44,700 --> 00:37:47,100
It's to die for. To die for?

408
00:37:47,100 --> 00:37:51,675
Yes, I ate Busan's Mil-myun for a long time!

409
00:37:51,675 --> 00:37:53,109
But this is the best.

410
00:37:53,109 --> 00:37:57,042
The noodles are soft yet so chewy!

411
00:37:57,042 --> 00:37:58,818
It seems like you know something.

412
00:37:58,818 --> 00:38:03,509
Yes, Father. You can't tell, but
my tongue is very sensitive.

413
00:38:03,509 --> 00:38:08,709
At last year's festival, Joon Gu made
and sold Dduk Bok Gi. It was really good.

414
00:38:08,709 --> 00:38:11,142
He's different than he looks.

415
00:38:11,142 --> 00:38:14,142
Well, appearance-wise your face
looks like a bear's feet...

416
00:38:14,142 --> 00:38:15,342
Beer feet?

417
00:38:15,342 --> 00:38:18,342
What? You didn't know?

418
00:38:19,330 --> 00:38:20,840
Eat up

419
00:38:21,275 --> 00:38:24,842
But why is the store named So Pal Bok Noodles?

420
00:38:25,290 --> 00:38:29,842
The name of Ha Ni grandmother's was Sok Pal Bok

421
00:38:29,842 --> 00:38:32,875
You mean you carried on the family business?

422
00:38:32,875 --> 00:38:34,909
That's right!

423
00:38:34,909 --> 00:38:40,242
My mother-in-law for 40 years and me for 20 years.

424
00:38:40,242 --> 00:38:41,742
Ohhhh~

425
00:38:41,742 --> 00:38:46,075
No wonder. A deep taste like this
can't come from an amateur.

426
00:38:46,075 --> 00:38:49,175
True! I learned while being hit.

427
00:38:49,175 --> 00:38:51,824
I wish my Ha Ni could carry on this business.

428
00:38:51,824 --> 00:38:57,509
She doesn't seem to have the
talent for cooking though.

429
00:38:58,375 --> 00:39:03,530
Don't worry, Father! Ha Ni and I...

430
00:39:03,530 --> 00:39:05,740
will together...do our very best!

431
00:39:06,409 --> 00:39:08,375
Hey! What's wrong with you?

432
00:39:08,375 --> 00:39:15,009
What? A store that's been around for
more than 60 years can't end just like that, right?

433
00:39:15,009 --> 00:39:21,675
Yeah, but it's not a bad idea to donate
everything back to society either.

434
00:39:21,675 --> 00:39:27,842
Father! Now I see you're the kind of
person who spits with a smile on your face.

435
00:39:28,775 --> 00:39:30,375
Ha Ni!

436
00:39:35,375 --> 00:39:37,762
Oh, Ha Ni!

437
00:39:44,075 --> 00:39:45,441
What's this?

438
00:39:53,609 --> 00:39:57,075
Hey, Bong Joon Gu, why are you
trying to destroy someone else's home?

439
00:39:57,075 --> 00:40:02,042
What are you on about?! This house is very stable.

440
00:40:18,042 --> 00:40:19,242
What is this?!

441
00:40:19,242 --> 00:40:20,275
Isn't it an earthquake?

442
00:40:20,275 --> 00:40:21,509
Earthquake?

443
00:40:21,509 --> 00:40:22,675
Dad, what are we gonna do?!

444
00:40:22,675 --> 00:40:25,730
It's okay. This is a new house. p

445
00:40:25,730 --> 00:40:28,770
It's stable... Very safe...

446
00:40:48,175 --> 00:40:49,942
Ha Ni!

447
00:40:53,809 --> 00:40:57,142
Get out! Father! Quickly!

448
00:40:57,142 --> 00:40:59,485
Hurry hurry come on!

449
00:41:21,975 --> 00:41:23,142
Ha Ni, are you alright?

450
00:41:23,142 --> 00:41:24,409
Wait a minute! Is everyone alright!?

451
00:41:24,409 --> 00:41:25,955
Yes!

452
00:41:26,863 --> 00:41:28,670
How could this happen!?

453
00:41:28,670 --> 00:41:30,228
Oh my!

454
00:41:30,300 --> 00:41:32,618
That's right! That... that...
That!

455
00:41:32,618 --> 00:41:33,309
What?

456
00:41:33,309 --> 00:41:35,233
That... that...just wait!

457
00:41:35,233 --> 00:41:36,442
Dad!

458
00:41:36,442 --> 00:41:38,769
No, you can't!

459
00:41:39,934 --> 00:41:41,734
Don't!

460
00:41:41,734 --> 00:41:42,906
I'll be back quickly!

461
00:41:42,906 --> 00:41:45,003
Don't worry!

462
00:42:34,329 --> 00:42:36,122
Dad...

463
00:42:38,152 --> 00:42:40,427
Da... Dad!

464
00:42:47,304 --> 00:42:52,076
At 5:30 this afternoon, there was a
mild earthquake of 2.0 magnitude in Seoul.

465
00:42:52,076 --> 00:42:55,620
It was a tremor that slightly shook windows, however...

466
00:42:55,620 --> 00:43:01,118
one house in this area, Yeonhee-dong, has collapsed, as you can see, to the point that it's unrecognizable.

467
00:43:01,118 --> 00:43:03,479
He's still in there! My dad is still in there...

468
00:43:03,479 --> 00:43:07,009
As far as we know there is still a person trapped within the collapsed house.

469
00:43:07,009 --> 00:43:09,609
The 2.0 magnitude YeonHee-dong
earthquake collapse site.
The rescue team is...

470
00:43:09,609 --> 00:43:12,192
...now in the process of clearing
a path and rescuing the person.

471
00:43:12,192 --> 00:43:14,009
Yes, I believe they're looking to see if anyone is there!!

472
00:43:14,009 --> 00:43:17,922
Yes! We can see someone's coming out
from under a table in the living room!

473
00:43:19,473 --> 00:43:22,559
Dad! Dad!

474
00:43:25,809 --> 00:43:28,942
What do you think this is, Dad!?

475
00:43:28,942 --> 00:43:30,909
Aigoo, I lived!

476
00:43:30,909 --> 00:43:33,926
- I'm alive! I'm alive!
- Daddy!

477
00:43:35,084 --> 00:43:37,609
Of course, there doesn't seem
to be any fatal injuries.

478
00:43:37,609 --> 00:43:41,906
The police suspect the collapse was caused by poor construction and are investigating the exact cause.

479
00:43:41,906 --> 00:43:43,775
Huh!?

480
00:43:43,775 --> 00:43:45,618
Oh Gi Dong?

481
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:48,000
Aigoo!

482
00:43:49,400 --> 00:43:52,000
Here... Huh?

483
00:43:55,842 --> 00:43:57,275
What is this?

484
00:43:58,437 --> 00:44:00,359
Was our house the only one...

485
00:44:00,359 --> 00:44:02,341
...that collapsed?

486
00:44:11,400 --> 00:44:13,200
Oh, really?

487
00:44:14,109 --> 00:44:16,209
Hehe... let's go.

488
00:44:17,342 --> 00:44:19,575
Gee... What!

489
00:44:26,075 --> 00:44:29,009
But, are you staying at a hotel again today?

490
00:44:29,009 --> 00:44:32,175
- Yeah.
- That must be really expensive.

491
00:44:32,175 --> 00:44:35,642
No, for now we decided to stay
at my dad's friend's house.

492
00:44:35,642 --> 00:44:38,375
At least until the house is rebuilt
or we find another one.

493
00:44:38,375 --> 00:44:40,442
We were contacted because of the newscast.

494
00:44:40,442 --> 00:44:42,809
Oh really? That's really great!

495
00:44:42,809 --> 00:44:44,475
Oh, is it her?

496
00:44:44,475 --> 00:44:46,109
What!?

497
00:44:54,909 --> 00:44:56,309
What the heck?

498
00:44:56,309 --> 00:44:58,642
Even pictures now...

499
00:45:00,709 --> 00:45:03,275
You're a total celebrity now.

500
00:45:03,275 --> 00:45:04,875
I'm sorry.

501
00:45:04,875 --> 00:45:09,075
Because of this unlucky friend,
you guys are suffering a lot.

502
00:45:10,275 --> 00:45:11,775
Let's go.

503
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:24,900
Please show your power of love. Thank you for your help.

504
00:45:24,900 --> 00:45:26,900
What are they doing?

505
00:45:26,900 --> 00:45:30,675
Of course you guys know about
what happened on the news...

506
00:45:30,675 --> 00:45:34,350
Our friend, Oh Ha Ni, lost her house overnight

507
00:45:34,350 --> 00:45:36,100
due to a sudden earthquake.

508
00:45:36,100 --> 00:45:39,800
Let's all help Ha Ni.

509
00:45:40,442 --> 00:45:42,175
What the heck is that?

510
00:45:42,175 --> 00:45:44,375
What is Bong Joon Gu doing?

511
00:45:44,375 --> 00:45:46,842
"Love's Fundraising?"

512
00:45:47,975 --> 00:45:50,109
That idiot!

513
00:45:50,109 --> 00:45:53,609
Hey, let's just go this way.

514
00:45:53,609 --> 00:45:55,109
Come on, follow me.

515
00:45:57,009 --> 00:45:59,109
Oh! Thank you.

516
00:45:59,109 --> 00:46:03,109
Thank you, let's help Ha Ni.
We're all friends aren't we?

517
00:46:03,109 --> 00:46:07,609
Show us the power of love!
Thank you!

518
00:46:07,609 --> 00:46:10,242
Oh, Ha Ni, Oh Ha Ni!

519
00:46:10,242 --> 00:46:13,109
Ha Ni, Ha Ni, move it, move it, move it!

520
00:46:13,109 --> 00:46:15,542
Hey, everyone, everyone, everyone!

521
00:46:16,942 --> 00:46:19,309
Please greet her with thunderous applause.

522
00:46:19,309 --> 00:46:21,142
Even after going through such a
horrible experience yesterday,

523
00:46:21,142 --> 00:46:25,575
